cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper proposes a hierarchical multi-agent reinforcement learning algorithm with unsupervised skill discovery for fully cooperative multi-agent settings. The paper focuses on the development of intelligent agents that can achieve high-level coordination by dynamically choosing complementary skills and executing primitive actions to perform these skills. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper also discusses the scalability and interpretability of the proposed method, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
